An overly serious. highbrow Troma release that doesn't really work. An update of the famous series of ancient Greek tragedies it is too pretentious, wordy and disjointed to have any impact for a modern audience or affectively convey it's themes. Add in the bad acting and shoestring budget and you left with a true lemon of a movie.

Troma isn't for everyone, but I really liked this movie. It's weirdly clean, but what works especially for me is how closely it hues to the traditional Greek play style. I think the movie has a lot of good ideas. It's not a masterpiece, but it's the dude's second movie.
